She wasn't sure what to think about all this.  First off, she sort of liked 
Quickstrike, but he hated her so she gave up on that idea.  She didn't know 
what to make of Scorponok.  He was a hard one to figure out.  One minute 
Scorponok would be nice and the next yell at her.  He even took the credit 
for finding the cave from her. She thought that all male bots must be the 
same, selfish, unfeeling and tempermental.  Well, at least mental.  She 
shrugged her shoulders and just plain gave up on any male bot liking her.  
It wan't the fact that she wasnb't good looking, she was very good looking.  
She guessed that she just didn't fit in well enough for the guys to even 
notice her.  She saw Stringtra flirt with Quickstrike.  And she remembered 
that Quickstrike had been flirting with Black Arachnia.
"Nah, he's taken by the others." she whispered to herself. She just didn't 
care anymore.  No bot would like her so why bother with trying.

She got up from the computer console and walked to the back of the cavern.  
She started to take measurements for an escape tunnel or two.
She sighed deeply and just told herself that her job is to obey Megatron. 
She remined herself that this was war and not a social party.
She went back to making the calculations for escape tunnels.
